I'll solve this task by calculating the requested financial ratios step by step.

## Debt to Equity Ratio
This measures the proportion of debt to equity used to finance a company's assets.
- Total Debt = Total Liabilities = $5,042,389.63
- Total Equity = $16,056,497.85
- Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Debt / Total Equity = $5,042,389.63 / $16,056,497.85 = 0.314

## Net Profit Margin
This measures how much net profit is generated as a percentage of revenue.
- Net Profit = $56,497.85
- Total Revenue = $547,392.30
- Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100% = ($56,497.85 / $547,392.30) × 100% = 10.32%

## Return on Assets (ROA)
This measures how efficiently a company is using its assets to generate profit.
- Net Profit = $56,497.85
- Total Assets (end of period) = $21,098,887.48
- ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100% = ($56,497.85 / $21,098,887.48) × 100% = 0.27%

## Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio
This measures how efficiently a company collects its receivables.
- Total Revenue = $547,392.30
- Accounts Receivable (end of period) = $200,359.99
- Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Accounts Receivable = $547,392.30 / $200,359.99 = 2.73
